laboratory_examinations.findings: The appendix is distended up to 13 mm with hyperemic wall and surrounding inflammatory changes. The kidney findings include a 1-cm hyperdensity in the right kidney consistent with a simple cyst, and a 1.4-cm hypodensity in the left kidney with indeterminate attenuation. No bowel obstruction, ascites or mesenteric adenopathy. Small amount of pelvic free fluid is seen.
